🚀 Shelby Protocol
Decentralized Hot Storage Infrastructure for Web3 & AI
An introduction to Shelby, a decentralized storage network designed to deliver cloud-level performance for data-intensive Web3 applications.
Shelby aims to solve one of the biggest infrastructure challenges in Web3: fast, scalable, and decentralized data access.
🌐 The Problem: Data Infrastructure in Web3
As the Web3 ecosystem grows, applications are becoming more complex and data-heavy.
However, most decentralized storage systems are optimized for cold storage rather than high-speed data access.
This creates several limitations:
⚠️ Slow data retrieval
⚠️ High latency for real-time applications
⚠️ Dependence on centralized cloud providers
⚠️ Limited scalability for AI and analytics workloads
For Web3 to compete with traditional Web2 systems, high-performance data infrastructure is essential.
⚡ What is Shelby?
Shelby is building a decentralized hot storage network that enables fast data retrieval while maintaining the benefits of decentralization.
Key goals of Shelby:
🔥 Low-latency data access
⚡ High throughput storage network
🌍 Decentralized infrastructure
🧠 Optimized for AI and real-time applications
Unlike traditional decentralized storage systems that focus on archival data, Shelby is designed for data that needs to be accessed frequently and quickly.
🧩 Why Hot Storage Matters
Modern Web3 applications require real-time data access.
Examples include:
🤖 AI Applications
AI models rely on continuous data streams for training and inference.
🎮 Web3 Gaming
Blockchain games require fast data processing and near-instant responses.
📊 Analytics & Dashboards
Real-time analytics platforms depend on fast data retrieval.
🌐 Social & Streaming Apps
Next-generation decentralized social platforms require scalable data infrastructure.
Shelby’s architecture aims to support these types of data-intensive workloads.
